# Rust Code Formatting Guidelines

## Overview
This project enforces consistent Rust code formatting using `rustfmt`. The CI pipeline automatically checks code formatting and will fail if code is not properly formatted.

## Pre-Commit Formatting Workflow

### 1. Format Your Code
Before committing any Rust code changes, always run:
```bash
cargo fmt
```

This will automatically format all Rust files in the project according to the standard Rust formatting rules.

### 2. Verify Formatting
To check if your code is properly formatted without making changes:
```bash
cargo fmt --check
```

